112
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:51,710
 I want to take pictures of people. 

113
00:07:51,710 --> 00:07:55,580
 Being too close to, bumping into, and bothering each other. 

114
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:58,050
 It felt nice. I wanted to keep doing it. 

115
00:07:58,050 --> 00:08:00,960
Yes, good! Good.

116
00:08:13,530 --> 00:08:17,310
I'm sorry the lunch is poor. I have more appointments later.

117
00:08:17,310 --> 00:08:19,270
Are you sure you put up the studio for sale?

118
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:23,280
I saw earlier that you're all booked for tomorrow and the day after.

119
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,950
I'm in the middle of putting it off.

120
00:08:24,950 --> 00:08:28,820
It's like homework that I have to do but really don't want to do.

121
00:08:28,820 --> 00:08:30,650
I don't know how they read my mind,

122
00:08:30,650 --> 00:08:33,680
but some people came saying that they're sad too,

123
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:37,940
that they will take a photo while they're here,

124
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:39,480
and that they would bring their family next time.

125
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:43,360
Thanks to that, I'm feeling relieved.

126
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:49,230
What if you lose your opportunity to work in Paris while doing that?

127
00:08:49,230 --> 00:08:52,650
Then it can't be helped. I'll just stay here longer.

128
00:08:55,150 --> 00:08:56,900
But what brings you here without a call?

129
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:58,700
Did something happen?

130
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:02,360
The Hills said that they would move us to the best spot.

131
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:04,000
Wow!

132
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,840
To be honest, it's nice.

133
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,800
When they told us to close up our store,

134
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:12,110
it felt so hopeless that I felt like I had sunken underground.

135
00:09:12,110 --> 00:09:17,000
But now I feel like I pulled through, that I made it...

136
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,950
That's great.

137
00:09:21,290 --> 00:09:27,150
 But... can I continue to be all right without you? 

138
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:33,910
How are the contract conditions from the people in Paris?

139
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:35,700
They aren't bad.

140
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:40,170
From their perspective, she is definitely an unknown designer.

141
00:09:42,550 --> 00:09:45,660
I'm sorry, that happens to be their perspective.

142
00:09:45,660 --> 00:09:48,200
So what did they say they would do for her?

143
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:51,390
Full control over design, control over personnel, profit shares,

144
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:56,280
and direct planning and participating in Paris fashion shows for two seasons.

145
00:09:56,280 --> 00:10:01,450
To be honest, this is an offer that would be difficult for any designer to decline.

146
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:06,400
Since you're doing it anyway, take care of each of those conditions one by one.

147
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:10,900
That kid, Yeong Eun, is like a daughter to me.

148
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:15,330
These are already good conditions, but go for something that would benefit her more.

149
00:10:15,330 --> 00:10:21,170
Instead of two seasons, make them promise something like a few full years.

150
00:10:21,170 --> 00:10:26,140
For the contract, be very meticulous and detailed while taking care of it.

151
00:10:27,470 --> 00:10:30,840
Yes, Father. I will take care of it well.

152
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:33,130
All right. That's all then.

153
00:10:33,690 --> 00:10:35,300
I'll trust you.

154
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:36,710
Okay.

155
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:58,920
 Your dad and that man are meeting alone. 

156
00:11:02,380 --> 00:11:03,930
CEO Seok?

157
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:05,620
Director Hwang.

158
00:11:06,820 --> 00:11:09,310
Why are you coming from there?

159
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:13,490
I had something urgent to report to CEO Hwang only.

160
00:11:13,490 --> 00:11:18,070
Urgent and only for him... What is it?

161
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,640
I told you that it was urgent and for him only,

162
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:24,460
so it's not something I can recklessly disclose.

163
00:11:24,460 --> 00:11:26,740
Of course, he wouldn't be able to say anything.

164
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:32,490
Since that "urgent, for him only" probably contains some kind of deal.

165
00:11:32,490 --> 00:11:35,960
They must have had some business to attend to as CEOs.

166
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:38,480
I think they were talking about you though.

167
00:11:39,350 --> 00:11:42,200
That's because I'm the common denominator between the two of them.

168
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,870
And he was put in charge of marketing for not only men's clothing line but also the rest of The One?

169
00:11:47,990 --> 00:11:49,840
That's because, on top of everything else, he's competent.

170
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:55,440
That's why. Aren't you getting the feeling that he approached you for business reasons?

171
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:57,170
What are you talking about?

172
00:11:57,860 --> 00:12:03,870
The reason why I like him is because he's not the kind of person that you're describing. Got it?

173
00:12:03,870 --> 00:12:06,150
CEO Hwang must really like him.

174
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:10,000
He even said that he would give him a 15% increase on his contractual fees.

175
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:15,930
You wrote that novel of yours in detail!

176
00:12:15,930 --> 00:12:17,260
I acknowledge your hard work!

177
00:12:17,260 --> 00:12:18,910
Confirm it.

178
00:12:23,190 --> 00:12:25,310
What is wrong with you?

179
00:12:25,310 --> 00:12:27,130
Why are you so confident?

180
00:12:27,130 --> 00:12:30,010
Because I genuinely love you.

181
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:37,920
Wow, I was so nervous!

182
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:40,800
You were the most wonderful, even among the professional models.

183
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,990
Really?

184
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:45,650
 Say "Mom, you're so cool!" 

185
00:12:46,260 --> 00:12:50,170
She was so pretty that I kept filming her without realizing it.

186
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:55,940
I get giddy from just looking at my daughter because of how much I adore her.

187
00:12:55,940 --> 00:13:02,030
After living my whole life alone, there were two of us after meeting my husband, then we became three...

188
00:13:02,030 --> 00:13:05,010
Whether I was pretty or ugly,

189
00:13:05,010 --> 00:13:08,890
they took my side and kept me from being lonely.

190
00:13:08,890 --> 00:13:13,060
If not family, who would do that for me?

191
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:15,080
That's true.

192
00:13:16,090 --> 00:13:20,920
Assistant Manager Seo, do you have any plans to start a family?

193
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:22,970
I'm not sure.

194
00:13:23,830 --> 00:13:27,100
I haven't met a good person like the senior manager yet.

195
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:41,290
You've been working with him for a long time, right?

196
00:13:41,290 --> 00:13:43,770
Yes, ever since I was hired.

197
00:13:43,770 --> 00:13:48,070
- What do you think of him, Assistant Manager Seo? 
 - Pardon?

198
00:13:48,070 --> 00:13:51,570
I was just wondering about what he's like from the perspective of someone working with him.

199
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:54,160
I see.

200
00:13:55,870 --> 00:13:58,580
He's someone I'm thankful for.

201
00:13:58,580 --> 00:14:03,970
In the beginning, I made a lot of mistakes and was criticized by clients.

202
00:14:03,970 --> 00:14:07,080
"That's all right. It happens."

203
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:10,370
He comforted me and cheered me on.

204
00:14:10,370 --> 00:14:14,890
So when the senior manager is around, I somehow feel safer,

205
00:14:14,890 --> 00:14:17,540
and I lean on him.

206
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:23,090
While working, that's how I feel.

207
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:29,460
Our Soo Ho is a pretty good man, I'll admit.

208
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:34,380
Am I taking too much of your time for giving something as small as one container of kimchi?

209
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:38,520
Not at all! Today was pretty relaxed because a large show has finished.

210
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:41,140
What do you usually do when you have free time?

211
00:14:41,140 --> 00:14:44,570
I go to the bookstore to look at magazines and go to popular places.

212
00:14:44,570 --> 00:14:46,670
These days I also go to the department store often.

213
00:14:46,670 --> 00:14:49,280
I can learn just from seeing what's displayed.

214
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:52,580
I'm sorry for taking away the time that you would be using to study.

215
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:55,510
These are photos from the fashion show.

216
00:14:55,510 --> 00:14:56,920
Thank you.

217
00:14:56,920 --> 00:15:01,460
Me too. I'll enjoy eating the kimchi.

